    <section id="install" class="row install-social-stream">
      <header>
        <h1>
          3
        </h1>
        <h2>
          Install Social Stream
        </h2>
      </header>

      <p>After deciding which Social Stream's components you will use for your application, you can install Social Stream, just adding the gems to your application's <code>Gemfile</code></p>

      <p>If you are using the full Social Stream suite, add <code>social_stream</code> to your <code>Gemfile</code></p>

      <pre>
gem 'social_stream'
      </pre>

      <p>On the other hand, if you are using the <code>social_stream-documents</code> and <code>social_stream-events</code> components only, add:</p>

         <pre>
gem 'social_stream-documents'
gem 'social_stream-events'
        </pre>

      Next, use <a href="http://gembundler.com/">Bundler</a>, the gem dependency manager to install all other gems required by your choice:

      <pre>
bundle
      </pre>

      <p>The next step is running the generators for the gems. If you are installing the full Social Stream's suite:</p>

      <pre>
rails generate social_stream:install
      </pre>

      <p>In the case you are installing certain components, you must run the generator per each one of them:</p>

      <pre>
rails generate social_stream:documents:install
rails generate social_stream:events:install
      </pre>

      Social Stream is not compatible with default mass attributes protection shipped with Rails 3.2.3, but uses the <a href="https://rubygems.org/gems/strong_parameters">strong_parameters gem</a> that will be the default in Rails 4. Set this in your <code>config/application.rb</code> before running the migration command:

      <pre>
config.active_record.whitelist_attributes = false
      </pre>

      Now migrate your database:

      <pre>
rake db:migrate
      </pre>

      Since Social Stream depends on <a href="https://github.com/plataformatec/devise">Devise</a>, make sure you follow its setup instructions. Specifically, make sure you set the default URL options for your environments at <code>config/environments/*.rb</code> with something like:

      <pre>
config.action_mailer.default_url_options = { :host => 'localhost:3000' }
      </pre>
    </section>


